After 1.5.30a, the project went dormant.  Payne's website
(@code{identicalsoftware.com/xwpe/}) remained online but no further
releases were made.

@section The Debian years (2002--2025)

@cindex Debian
@cindex Francesco Paolo Lovergine
@cindex Andreas Tille
@cindex Jari Aalto

xwpe entered Debian in 2002, maintained by Francesco Paolo Lovergine.
Over the following two decades, the Debian package accumulated patches
to keep xwpe building with evolving toolchains:

@itemize @bullet
@item Jari Aalto: manpage hyphen fixes, @code{strcpy()} macro workaround.
@item Francesco P.@: Lovergine: format-security fixes, tparm prototype
      disable, missing prototype for @code{print_to_end_of_buffer()}.
@item Andreas Tille: Salsa migration, modern packaging standards.
@item Helmut Grohne: cross-build fix (@code{--host} to @command{configure}).
@item Robert Millan: architecture list fix.
@end itemize

By 2025, xwpe had accumulated 9 patches and was failing to build with
GCC 15 (Debian bug #1098180) due to the C23 default where @code{f()}
means @code{f(void)}.

@section GitHub forks (2017--2019)

@cindex Guus Bonnema
@cindex Alessandro Magnasco

Alessandro G.@: Magnasco hosted a GitHub fork at
@code{github.com/amagnasco/xwpe}.  Guus Bonnema contributed two
important fixes:

@enumerate
@item Fix for a link error: renamed @code{WpeGpmInit} prototype to
      the actual function name @code{WpeGpmMouseInit} in @file{edit.h}.
@item Fix for a segfault on early @code{MALLOC} failure in
      @file{we_main.c}.
@end enumerate

Jan D@"orntlein also forked the code on GitHub but made no significant
changes.  Both forks went dormant.

@section The rescue (2026)

@cindex Codeberg
@cindex v1.5.31
@cindex v1.6.0
@cindex v1.6.1
@cindex SCREENCELL

In May 2026, Juan Manuel M@'endez Rey contacted Dennis Payne, who
gave his explicit blessing for a new maintainer.  The rescue proceeded
in three releases:

@table @strong
@item v1.5.31 (rescue release)
Baseline: Payne 1.5.30a + 2 cherry-picks from Bonnema + all 7 Debian
patches as proper upstream commits with original authors preserved.
Closed Debian #1098180 (GCC 15 FTBFS) and #228820 (22-year-old color
dialog crash).

@item v1.6.0 (UTF-8 and resize)
Replaced the 1993 byte-based screen buffer with the @code{SCREENCELL}
buffer model for native UTF-8 display.  Added terminal resize via
@code{KEY_RESIZE}, keyboard remapping for modern terminals, GPM safety
check, and 20 automated tests.

@item v1.6.1 (modern autotools)
Replaced the 1998 hand-written build system (1,500 lines of custom
@file{aclocal.m4} macros for SCO/HP-UX/AIX portability) with standard
@command{configure.ac} + @command{Makefile.am}.  @code{./configure &&
make} works out of the box with any modern compiler.

@item v1.6.2 (compiler and debugger resurrection)
Complete SCREENCELL migration for popup save/restore.  Compiler
integration for 5 languages: gcc, g++, gfortran, fpc, javac with
error navigation.  Debugger resurrection: fixed 30-year-old pipe fd
leak, SIGCHLD handler, SIGPIPE crash.  Added jdb as 5th debugger
backend (Java).  Pty-based program output capture (zero flicker).
Restored User Screen (Ctrl-G P) broken since Payne era.  12-chapter
Texinfo manual with restored content from Kruse's 1.4 manpage.
560+ historical files archived.  Emacs-compatible cursor keys.
@end table

The new upstream home is @uref{https://codeberg.org/mendezr/xwpe}.
Historical archive: @uref{https://codeberg.org/mendezr/xwpe-archives}.
